The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, January 17, 2004 				 Chill adieu in the air
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Last week, a city wrapped in a blanket of fog all but froze over. But by this weekend, the winter of 04 appears to be on its way out.																								Weather officials at Alipore said on Friday that there were slim chances of the mercury dropping further this month, unless a low-pressure zone formed suddenly, drawing in the North Wind.																								There has been a change in the wind pattern since Thursday, following a sudden upper-air circulation off the Sunderbans, pushing up the mercury.																								Officials at Alipore said that the minimum temperature recorded on Friday was 16.8 degrees Celsius, three degrees above normal.
